FBIS4-64543 "drweu086_q_94010" FBIS-WEU-94-086 Daily Report 30 Apr 1994 TURKEY PKK Opens `Information' Office in Madrid PKK Opens `Information' Office in Madrid NC0405082294 Istanbul HURRIYET in Turkish 30 Apr 94 p 16 NC0405082294 Istanbul HURRIYET Turkish BFN [Report by Zeynel Lule: "A PKK Office in Spain"] [Excerpt] Strasbourg--The Workers Party of Kurdistan [PKK] has opened an office in Madrid under the guise of a Kurdish Information Center. The opening ceremony on 27 April was attended by many members of parliament and several representatives of ERNK [Kurdish People's Liberation Front], which is the PKK's armed wing. The daily EL PAIS has reported that Faruk Dogru, a representative of ERNK, addressed the ceremony and urged the Spanish Government to direct pressure on Turkey. He also said that Spain's support would be sought in the struggle through the center in Madrid and initiatives launched with the Spanish Government for a military embargo against Turkey. [passage omitted]
